node.statement: CASE 1a - g_3 analysis. CURRENT STATE: B contains {1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, a_1, ..., a_n, b_1, ..., b_k}. OBSERVATION: supp(g_3) = {2, 3, 5, 6, c_1, ..., c_m}. Therefore {2, 3, 5, 6} is contained in both B and supp(g_3), so B intersects supp(g_3) non-trivially (contains at least 4 elements). CASE SPLIT: Either g_3(B) = B (Case 1a-i) or g_3(B) is not equal to B (Case 1a-ii).
